    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
            <title>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lower splined end of the column shaft into the upper universal joint of the
                    lower steering shaft. Align the marks made in
                    <hotlnk document="s05008t_7.xml" xrefid="hl0500802">Step 2 of REMOVE, STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY
                        <xref refid="hl0500802"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bolt steering column to steering column support bracket. Tighten as specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s05008t_12.xml" xrefid="hl0500801">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0500801"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install pinch bolt to secure the upper universal joint to the steering column. Use a new
                    shear-type lock nut. Tighten as specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s05008t_12.xml" xrefid="hl0500801">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0500801"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the the dimmer switch wiring to the steering column wiring harness. Connect the
                    steering column wiring harness to the harness platform.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
